[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating application classes**\n\nI’m considering the default build-time for application classes. Many classes are initialized at build time, and if `org.objenesis.instantiator.perc.PercInstantiator` is initialized, its static fields remain null. At runtime, they reset to null. However, I wonder about the constant folding of `getstatic class$java$lang$Class` as `Class.class`. The coverage dynamic access report seems to rely on static analysis during native-image build, so maybe it's tracking methods that are reachable instead of actual runtime behavior.\n\n**Assessing dynamic calls**\n\nI’m looking into dynamic calls in code and whether call site coverage can be analyzed with a JVM tracking agent rather than natively. If the JVM resets should work given the test order, we might need to check the field names with \"$\" in them. Although it seems Checkstyle doesn’t restrict these, the coverage report indicates no newly covered call sites, possibly due to class cache initialization issues. I’ll need to ensure both tests clear caches appropriately for accurate coverage.\n\n**Exploring JVM instrumentations**\n\nI’m wondering if running both tests in the same JVM class is causing some issues with dynamic access coverage. After the first attempt, it seems like getDeclaredMethod was covered, but the class$ wasn’t, possibly due to how it’s invoked with the class literal. I'm looking for ways to force a direct call to class$. Using reflection isn’t preferred unless absolutely necessary, especially since the target is package-private. Maybe I could generate a class with JavaCompiler or ByteBuddy instead, but I’m also considering leveraging isolated classloaders for a fresh start without reflection.\n\n**Evaluating class loading options**\n\nI'm considering whether loading a class with the same name from a library jar could impact the outcome. It seems like using URLClassLoader might work for testing, but native-image restricts dynamic class loading, which isn't very friendly. I could also explore transforming bytecode like in a previous test, but ByteBuddy isn't available in this version. Maybe I can achieve class initialization isolation by invoking a constructor in a separate JVM, but that feels off for native. Resetting with VarHandle or Unsafe doesn’t seem viable either; synthetic static field names might create issues in metadata.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0570ed50c56ed7a30169ef7413a0948196994167229ec2eb68\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp73QmyqqYOYuVdS0PID9z-kroM5wWIys6r1-RCfAQfzl2_TJN93eif0kyYcinloPcYmtZv1nUMzvaUCeC3E1PWJ7Kjg49roZzg1Noar_4DVPjuJQ65yL3UTz203FJ8y-dimUQ3ntl40C43UjIYaQ048WLLC1-8Pg8pd1w6Yc6mHd4fwweWCPF-5avYcT3lcbdzOKTpRPmagyhkBHkGI_ywzdEvQCLd8I47AipcwQSKUma3vwlbUAQ4N09ZAvcyu0fw33WE5dAWcyu8P-1X8nVUTh8p6Mot-U_TEnrHn1jGcKSEBwXHuZrI3KprMz0cRlXY6q8nsaryT-EZ_ApDMzfMtXMsjrjp2nNYWV6YT-M-EZEEKZ14b1lavRy2ykiihCxhZ537cx6fGINrYUv-skeRea_aTRrvyhtR17Hp2NHrwcnBE6AaMUyRT3MbDGLSTEXByDSev4trR8scN8tjXcGP1uPNZyL_eRF5LDxhQeczmE-GZatONCCoBWPkRNqZarTCVPlRV1zNyNpzJkOJ7w4aSAhkA0vN82ak6QzBHvsE6LgzrHvc_stlD_wxECiN5aKFvX4t9URzC9BFsA23L0ZJkhFtd5TDlj_9hP-j_5V4uzBcok3sb16ryBU69B1NqvVyap4sShWzA4lTSmg5z_tgdIfvsHBCBESEnIaWYxuuD7qF9UvZAqK7gyiME5ZMNVv9Hghofa9FErfn3BJFE2ApJZcssePYvStaodIg7sijgTzzFU4bu--dXZh2un0TDI4Kn47VEVq_ph9rwJABqsOjYiLJxXa33l1kleO-VFelpD4bapucQdxOFVPH-jBRE6evSEUxG3MhlVH2fBOZhOzDfQVRMqLgs9_VZx_mAHqD3q-d4O3_uA2HZReab2zvTj-te1CGT39PAL_heBPwD_TDlOY_f8vtIYwcLL2NSdTUxS1slXYx2oR7w7A40vs9RhAFe8Z3yv3OEwC2c1K9YIix_qP9EeJ9_dsRKpCn_3htr3AWcGkFRuq4oDAF-OLuybWI67uXbp2JkvQgi1ulkZpZJ4lv1mTsLTz-VMh-ajsfaZw5Oy45FUZh_sqMR9YAS5976mOXlTOT6qX85p3Ij2FY4VEy9HpEcdqZkWX_eXIDegcHW5e0KDhI-jiexgoMWetvqP9Xf8YYe-oPCZwrVfpQa4_YxdkcbkBnpwPgD_Gv0bzqPTOv4DgjwRW-y4LGn_UXBGYMgmy85Gem-wUTq_c7RWjoti3S9ASODk9rFp4hYDEugl8IHH80O_FjW_uTwxZXByXKaR6Y6XWHeGXQAFex7qCU8QxiNYHz2r01nSdh7wbNLafMZjev9di-kBgkn-xAv3PIeoLcFQpqHQJvkI_yflRBPKAShFzd